    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "it's not even about triggers anymore. it's just how things are. i try to fix it, i try to be better, and it just results in the same mess every single time. it feels like there's no way out of the pattern. i'm just so done with trying to fight something that never changes.",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "It sounds incredibly disheartening to feel like your efforts are futile and that the pattern is unbreakable. When you try to \"fix\" things and they immediately revert, it can make you feel like you're fighting a losing battle against something fundamental about yourself or your circumstances. That exhaustion of constant fighting is a heavy burden to carry.\n\nSometimes, the most powerful thing you can do when you feel like you're stuck in a loop is to stop trying to force a solution and instead just observe the pattern without judgment. You don't have to fix it right this second, or even today. You can just sit with the feeling of being stuck and acknowledge that it's okay to not be okay for a moment.\n\nWould you like to explore what happens in those moments when you feel like you've finally \"got it together\" but then everything falls apart? Or perhaps you'd prefer to just vent about how tired you feel of the cycle?",
